description = Use when designing or reviewing a tool/function an agent will call, or when looking up or saving a tool-design practice — not when wording the instruction in general (that is prompt-engineering) or managing what already occupies the window (that is context-engineering). Retrieve, capture, or refresh distilled tool-design knowledge on demand — the tool/function contract an agent calls: descriptions, input/output schemas, granularity and consolidation, namespacing, high-signal and token-efficient returns, error-message design, structured output, and tool evals.
